                    </div>
                    <span>I had long heard nothing but great things about "Liar's Poker" but it was not until I found myself in an airport bookstore before a cross-country "red eye" that I decided to read it.  It was no disappointment--the book reads like a novel, and Mr. Lewis blends a perfect mixture of sardonic irreverence with a traders' "greed" to land the bull's eye.  As someone familiar with bond trading, "Liar's Poker" was still informative and an enjoyable read; and quick too--the entire book was finished by the time my flight landed in LA! </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A  Wall Street Classic</div>
                    <div>
